---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import me from "../assets/me.jpeg";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
	<article class="pt-2 sm:pt-10">
		<section class="py-6">
			<div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-2 md:gap-4">
				<Image
					src={me}
					width={me.width}
					height={me.height}
					alt="Nicolò D'Addabbo"
					class="rounded-full my-4 w-20 h-20"
					loading="eager"
				/>
				<h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">
					Nicolò D&apos;Addabbo
				</h1>
			</div>
			<p class="mt-4 font-light">Software Engineer. Berlin-based.</p>
			<p class="mt-4">
				Currently working on Applied AI at <a
					class="link text-lg font-semibold"
					href="https://tesla.com"
					target="_blank">Tesla</a
				>, across software engineering, data engineering, design, and AI agents.
				End to end on everything, from business and design to development.
			</p>
			<p class="mt-4 font-light">
				I studied Computer Science and Engineering between <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="https://polimi.it">Milan</a
				>, <a class="link" target="_blank" href="https://www.upc.edu"
					>Barcelona</a
				>, and <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="https://www.unibo.it">Bologna</a
				>. I started building things right after high school by going
				door to door in my hometown, <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rimini">Rimini</a
				>, asking local businesses if they needed a website. A few said
				yes. That led to better gigs, and eventually to more complex
				mobile apps and internal tools. Along the way, I&apos;ve
				developed a strong interest in clean architecture and building
				software that&apos;s genuinely useful to people.
			</p>
			<p class="mt-4 font-light">
				I&apos;ve been a musician, Ultimate Frisbee player, and event
				organizer.
			</p>
			<p class="mt-4 font-light">
				You can find me on <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicolodaddabbo/"
					>LinkedIn</a
				>, <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="https://github.com/nicolodaddabbo/">GitHub</a
				> or send me an email at <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="mailto:nicolodaddabbo@gmail.com"
					>nicolodaddabbo@gmail.com</a
				>
			</p>
		</section>
		<section class="py-6">
			<h2 class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase opacity-50">Projects</h2>
			<ul class="mt-4 flex flex-col gap-y-5">
				<li class="font-light">
					<a
						class="link"
						target="_blank"
						href="https://github.com/vistal-dev/vistal"
						>Vistal</a
					>: Authorization layer for AI agents. Row-level security,
					field-level permissions, and per-user access control so LLMs
					can query databases without prompt-injection vulnerabilities.
				</li>
				<li class="font-light">
					<a
						class="link"
						target="_blank"
						href="https://github.com/nicolodaddabbo/thing"
						>Nudge</a
					>: TypeScript library with a generative CLI for building
					prompts in code.
				</li>
				<li class="font-light">
					<a
						class="link"
						target="_blank"
						href="https://schedule.paganello.com"
						>Paganello Schedule</a
					>: Web app for displaying real-time match schedules for
					Paganello, the world&apos;s largest Beach Ultimate Frisbee
					tournament. Over 3,000 players and attendees rely on it, which
					deepened my interest in building software that solves real problems.
				</li>
				<li class="font-light">
					<a
						class="link"
						target="_blank"
						href="https://github.com/nicolodaddabbo/hykee-ai"
						>HYKEE AI</a
					>: A virtual assistant that helps financial analysts interpret
					Italian company balance sheets, featuring fine-tuned language
					models and in-context learning strategies.
				</li>
				<li class="font-light">
					<a
						class="link"
						target="_blank"
						href="https://amslaurea.unibo.it/id/eprint/33714/"
						>LLMs for Financial Statement Analysis</a
					> (in Italian): Conducted as part of the HYKEE AI project, it
					includes a comparative study between open-source and proprietary
					LLMs, evaluated through expert-labeled data and a fine-tuned
					"LLM-as-a-Judge" model.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</article>
</Layout>
